Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} lengthways and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{190%g}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled @water{500%ml} for the stock into a #measuring jug{}. Add the @vegetable stock paste{20%g} and stir well to combine - this is your veg stock.

> See pantry for amount of water.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal saucepan and transfer to an ovenproof dish later.

Once hot, add the garlic and @risotto rice{175%g}. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir your veg stock into the pan and bring back to the boil.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the bottom shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Roasted Peppers and Tomatoes ==

In the meantime, pop the pepper onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Pop the tomatoes onto a piece of foil. Drizzle over some @oil{} and the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Add to the baking tray with the pepper.

Roast on the top shelf until the pepper is soft and slightly charred and the tomatoes are softened, ~{15-18%minutes}.

== Finishing Touches ==

When your risotto is cooked, remove from the oven and stir through the @butter{10%g}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, roasted pepper and three quarters of the @fresh pesto{100%g}.

Carefully spoon the juices from the balsamic tomatoes into the risotto and mix through.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Share your pesto risotto between your #bowls{}.

Top with the balsamic tomatoes and drizzle over the remaining pesto to finish.

Enjoy!